                  </hi>. On the evening of the 27th of February, I saw the prisoners in company a little before eight o'clock—I saw Hardy go to Mr. Moore's shop, Slaterstood by his side—Hardy, took this umbrella down, turned round, and gave it to Slater—I took Hardy, and pulled him along, and took Slater with the other hand—I put them into a shoe-maker's shop, and took them into custody.</p>
